dcterms:creator: P. Marler
L. Hobbett
dcterms:description: Chimpanzee pant-hoots are vocal sequences composed of up to four acoustically distinct phases, typically produced in a specific order. The dataset includes annotated recordings of isolated pant-hoots produced during various contexts.
dcterms:title: Chimpanzee Data Set

dcterms:creator: M. Hardus
dcterms:description: The orangutan dataset includes recordings of long calls, which are complex vocalizations composed of various phases. The dataset features spontaneous long calls and those produced in response to environmental stimuli.
dcterms:title: Orangutan Data Set

dcterms:creator: I. Schamberg
D. L. Cheney
Z. Clay
G. Hohmann
R. M. Seyfarth
dcterms:description: The bonobo dataset consists of high-hoots and other vocalizations, including a variety of call types. The dataset captures the complexity of bonobo communication and includes recordings of different call types.
dcterms:title: Bonobo Data Set
